                <div class="content new-content">
                    <div class="fw-semibold fs-5-5 color-primary lh-base mb-3">
                        Dai Nam University (school code DDN) announces enrollment for full-time university program in 2025.
                    </div>
                    <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Dai Nam University announced enrollment information for 2025, accordingly, the University will enroll 9,500 students for 43 majors/training programs with 3 admission methods.</strong></span></p>
<h2><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>1. Recruitment area: Recruitment nationwide</strong></span></h2>
<h2><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>2. School code: DDN</strong></span></h2>
<h2><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>3. Admission quota: 9500</strong></span></h2>
<h2><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>4. Admission objects: Candidates graduated from high school or equivalent</strong></span></h2>
<h2><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>5. Admission method</strong></span></h2>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Method 1:</strong> Admission based on 2025 high school graduation exam results</span></li>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Method 2:</strong> Admission based on 12th grade high school transcripts</span></li>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Method 3:</strong> Direct admission according to regulations of the Ministry of Education and Training and the School</span></li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Note: The conversion of admission methods to the same starting point of 30 is carried out according to the guidance documents of the Ministry of Education and Training.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>6. Admission requirements</strong></span></h2>
<h3><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Method 1: Admission based on 2025 high school graduation exam results</strong></span></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><em>Consider the 2025 high school graduation exam scores of 03 subjects in the admission combination</em></span></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Admission score &#61; (Subject 1 score &#43; Subject 2 score &#43; Subject 3 score) &#43; Priority score (if any).</span></li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><em>Priority points: Priority points for region and subject (according to current Admission Regulations).</em></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Quality assurance threshold (floor score) of Method 1: Admission score reaches the floor score set by the School after the 2025 high school graduation exam results are available, except for the Health Sector, set by the Ministry of Education and Training.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Method 2: Admission based on 12th grade high school transcripts</strong></span></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><em>Consider the entire 12th grade high school transcript scores of 03 subjects in the admission group</em></span></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Admission score &#61; (Subject 1 score &#43; Subject 2 score &#43; Subject 3 score)</span></li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">In there:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Subject 1 score &#61; Average score of the whole 12th grade year of subject 1</span></li>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Subject 2 score &#61; Average score of the whole 12th grade year of subject 2</span></li>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Subject 3 score &#61; Average score of the whole 12th grade year of subject 3</span></li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><em>Note: The school does not add priority points for the transcript review method.</em></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">The quality assurance threshold (floor score) of Method 2 is specified as follows:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Medicine and Pharmacy majors must have a grade 12 academic record of Excellent and a total score of 3 subjects according to the admission combination of 24 points or higher.</span></li>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Nursing major must have a grade 12 academic record of Good or higher and a total score of 3 subjects according to the admission combination of 19.5 points or higher.</span></li>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Other majors: Total score of 3 subjects according to the admission combination is from 18 points or higher.</span></li>
</ul>
<h3><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Method 3: Direct admission according to regulations of the Ministry of Education and Training and the School</strong></span></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Direct admission of candidates who meet the requirements for direct admission according to the regulations of the Ministry of Education and Training and Dai Nam University.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>7. Admission quota, subject combinations for admission and tuition fees</strong></span></h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Admission quota, subject combinations for admission and tuition fees of Dai Nam University in 2025 (calculated by semester, each year has 03 semesters). Detailed information is presented in the table below:</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><img src="https://atm273446-s3user.vcos.cloudstorage.com.vn/dhdainam/thumbnail/images/posts/57710/image-thumb__57710__optimizeSizeThumbnail/hptk9elmr76k754ohfeq20250321094916_thump_1743494318.2e2c9da3.jpg" alt="hptk9elmr76k754ohfeq20250321094916_thump.jpg" width="900" /></span></p>
<h2><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>8. Application form</strong></span></h2>
<h3><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>For method 1: Consider the results of the 2025 high school graduation exam</strong></span></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Candidates register their admission wishes (unlimited number) to the School according to the general regulations of the Ministry of Education and Training on university admissions in 2025. After being admitted, the School will send a notice of admission with specific documents to be submitted.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>For method 2: Consider high school transcripts of grades 1</strong></span> <span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>and 2</strong></span></h3>
<ul style="text-align: justify;">
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">01 Notarized copy of High School/Vocational Education Transcript of 3 years of study.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">01 Notarized copy of citizen identification card (both sides).</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">01 Application form according to Dai Nam University&#039;s form.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">01 Notarized copy of high school diploma (Only applicable to candidates graduating before 2025).</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Application fee: 50,000 VND/application</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">For method 3: Direct admission</span></strong></h3>
<ul style="text-align: justify;">
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">01 Application form for direct admission and priority admission;</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">01 Notarized copy of Certificate of winning prizes in competitions (if any) or Certificate of being an official member of the team participating in the competitions (if any).</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">01 Notarized copy of High School/Vocational Education Transcript of 3 years of study.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">01 Notarized copy of citizen identification card (both sides).</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">01 Notarized copy of high school diploma (Only applicable to candidates graduating before 2025).</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Application fee: 50,000 VND/application</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">9. Time to receive application documents and admission fees</span></strong></h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Dai Nam University will organize admissions in many batches/year, expected as follows:</span></p>
<ul style="text-align: justify;">
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Receive application documents based on transcripts: from the date of admission information release.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Admission round for all methods according to general regulations of the Ministry of Education and Training: according to the plan of the Ministry of Education and Training.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Additional admission round: The school will announce specifically after the end of the general admission round of the Ministry of Education and Training.</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Application fee:</span></strong></p>
<ul style="text-align: justify;">
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Application fee: 50,000 VND/application.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Registration fee on the Ministry&#039;s General Admissions system: According to the general regulations of the Ministry of Education and Training.</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">10. Application form and receipt of application documents</span></strong></h2>
<ul style="text-align: justify;">
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Admission round for all methods according to the general regulations of the Ministry of Education and Training: All candidates register their wishes on the general information portal of the Ministry of Education and Training.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Other rounds: Candidates perform 3 steps:</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Step 1:</strong> Register for admission online at: <a href="https://xettuyen.dainam.edu.vn/">https://xettuyen.dainam.edu.vn/</a></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Fill out the online application at: <a href="https://hosoxettuyen.dainam.edu.vn/">https://hosoxettuyen.dainam.edu.vn/</a></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Send hard copy documents according to regulations to Dai Nam University:</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Submit your application in person or by express mail to the address: Admissions Office - Dai Nam University, No. 1 Pho Xom, Phu Lam, Ha Dong, Hanoi.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Hotline: 0931 595 599/ 0961 595 599/ 0971 595 599.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Contact information</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Admissions Office – Dai Nam University</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Address: Room 105, Central Building – No. 01 Pho Xom, Phu Lam, Ha Dong, Hanoi.</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Call hotlines: 0961595599 / 0931595599 / 0971595599</span></p>
</li>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Send Zalo message: 0961595599 / 0931595599 / 0971595599</span></p>
</li>
<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 14pt;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Inbox Fanpage Dai Nam University: <a href="https://www.facebook.com/DAINAM.EDU.VN/">https://www.facebook.com/DAINAM.EDU.VN/</a></span></p>
</li>
